//Tekstovi 
 Insomniac aims to help people with chronic insomnia to learn about and tract factors that have been shown to improve sleep quality. Find out which factors are the most important for you by using our build-in statistical methods and graphs. 

 Insomniac is not intended for use in the diagnosis of disease or other conditions, or in the cure, mitigation, treatment or prevention of disease. If you have troubles initiating and staying asleep, you should talk to your health care provider. Psychological research have shown that scheduling a time of the day for worrying about problems is a good way to decrease worry, anxiety and insomnia (see 8, 9). During the evening, write down your biggest problems and postpone thinking about them for the certain part of the following day.
